Usage: pantry command [options] arguments

COMMANDS THAT ACCEPT OPTIONS
============================
find tag-name pattern [ tag-name pattern... ]
       Search for foods using specified tag names and patterns
all
       Select all foods in database
create
       Create a new food
id id [ id... ]
       Select foods with specified IDs

Options for the find, all, create, and id commands
==================================================

PATTERN CONTROL
    -i, --ignore-case
        makes all patterns case insensitive
    -v, --invert
        invert ordinary matching behavior
    --within
        use "within" matcher (default)
    --posix
        use POSIX regular expression matcher
    --pcre
        use PCRE regular expression matcher
    --exact
        use "exact" matcher

CHANGE TAGS AND PROPERTIES
    -c tag-name string, --change-tag tag-name string
        Set tag equal to string
    -u pattern, --change-unit pattern
        Change current unit to the one matching pattern
    -q number,  --change-quantity number
        Change quantity to number, which may be floating point,
        a fraction, or a mixed number
    --change-percent-refuse number
        Change percent refuse to number (between 0 and 100 inclusive)
    --change-yield number
        Change yield to number, which is a floating-point number

    --by-nutrient nut-name qty
        set quantity of foods so amount of nut-name = qty
    -r, --refuse
        reduce quantity of foods by percent refuse

CHANGING NUTRIENTS, AVAILABLE UNITS, AND INGREDIENTS
    --change-nutrient pattern value
        change nutrient value
    --rename-nutrient pattern new-name
        rename nutrient to new-name
    --delete-nutrients pattern
        delete nutrients matching pattern

    --change-available-unit pattern value
        change available unit value
    --rename-available-unit pattern new-name
        rename available unit matching pattern to new-name
    --delete-available-units pattern
        delete available units matching regexp

    --add-as-ingredients id
        Add selected foods as ingredients to food with id

ADDING CHANGED FOODS
    -a, --append
        Add changed foods to the end of the database
    --prepend
        Add changed foods to the beginning of the database

REPORTING
    -p REPORT, --print REPORT
        print REPORT, where REPORT is one of:
            name - name tag, if food has one
            properties - all non-tag properties
            units - available units
            paste - name, available units, and IDs for cut-and-paste
            count-tags - summary of tag information
            nutrients - nutrients of each food
            total - total nutrients
            ingredients - a food's ingredients
            tags - the food's tags
            blank - a blank line
            xml - XML output (maybe for XSLT, or XSL-FO, or . . . )

    -g nutrient-name number, --goal nutrient-name number
        Show nutrient-name in nutrients and Nutrients reports, with
        number used as a goal
    --show-all-nutrients
        Show all nutrients in nutrients and Nutrients reports,
        even if --goal is used
    --show-tag tag-name, -t tag-name
        Show tag-name in tags and summarize-tags reports
    --show-all-tags
        Show all tags in tags and summarize-tags reports,
        even if --show-tag is used
    --one-column
        Print values in one column for tags and properties reports

Additional options for the all, find, and id commands
=====================================================
In addition to the options shown above, these
options are available for the all, find, and id
commands. (They are not available for the create
command.)

SORTING OPTIONS
    -k tag-name, --key-ascending tag-name
        Sort by tag-name in ascending order
    -K tag-name, --key-descending tag-name
        Sort by tag-name in descending order
    -O tag-name value, --key-order tag-name value
        Show values for tag-name in a particular order

EDITING AND DELETING FOODS
    --edit
        Edit foods in place
    --delete
        delete matching foods

INGREDIENTS
    --export-ingredients
	Add ingredients of selected foods to database
    --remove-ingredients
        Remove all ingredients of selected foods

Additional options for the all and find commands
================================================
In addition to the options shown above, these
options are available for the all and find commands.

    --head n
        Remove all but the first n foods from the
        selection
    --tail n
        Remove all but the last n foods from the
        selection

COMMANDS THAT DO NOT ACCEPT OPTIONS
===================================
These commands do not accept any of the options
shown above. Some of these commands do accept (or require)
arguments following the name of the command.

open filename
	Close current file and open new one
append-file filename
       Add contents of filename to end of the database
prepend-file filename
       Add contents of filename to the beginning of the database
close
	Close currently open file
save {filename}
	Save contents of current file
quit
	Shut down server
status
       Current server status
help
       show this help message
version
       Print version information
copyright
       Print copyright and license information
move id id [ id... ]
       Rearrange foods with specified IDs into specified sequence

Pantry home page: http://www.smileystation.com/pantry
